{"key":"post-16277254","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>16277254</id>\n<content>Simply pour a glass or two of water around the edges.&amp;nbsp; If the substrate floats, it's OK, but not necessary.&amp;nbsp; After an hour or so, tilt the tray on its side and pour the excess water off.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Don't worry if a bit of water is left over on the bottom.&amp;nbsp; You're not going to soak it long enough to reach saturation, so that water will be absorbed over the next few hours.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We soak brf cakes for 24 hours, but one to two is usually enough for bulk substrates because the mycelium mat isn't as dense as cakes.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;If I accepted cultivation PMs, I would either have to ignore them or never post in the forums because I was getting up to 100 per day when I put that notice up a few years ago. Thanks for understanding.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>16278029</next>\n<prev>16277041</prev>\n<first>16272857</first>\n<last>16278317</last>\n<when>1337866224</when>\n<utime>05/24/12 04:30 PM</utime>\n</post>"}